property.name: text
property.value: Simulation of a three-state Hidden Markov Model with Gaussian emissions. The Observation Sequence plot displays the generated samples that are drawn from a Gaussian distribution. The mean and standard deviation of the observed variable depends on the hidden state. The initial probability distribution over the hidden states is specified by immediate transitions from an init state to the three hidden states.

property.name: text
property.value:
A: Transition Probability Matrix pi: Prior Probability Distribution m: Vector of means. sigma: Vector of standard deviations
At state i, samples are distributed according to Y ~ N( m(i), sigma(i)
